DID-23.Description of CMU Components:
Unit 5 is a Cogenation unit which produces both steam and power. Unit 5 is the largest generating unit at Fawley refinery. This Generating Unit forms the 'E_FAWN-1' BMU on its own and is part of the larger site inclusive BM Trading Unit, 'EPCO1'. 

All Components of EMG-19, EMD-19 are located within the physical boundaries of the Esso Petroleum Company,Limited, Oil Refinery at Esso Refinery - Fawley - Southampton - Hampshire - SO45 1TX - United Kingdom. 

Unit 5 is one of three power and steam generation units on site and is a Gas Turbine CHP plant. It is connected to the Local Distribution Network (LDN) at 132kV level at the Fawley North Sub-Station (MSID 7081).  Unit 5 is a licensed generator.

Unit 5 has various auxiliary load equipment-  the power for which is supplied from another part of the LDN Fawley North Sub-Station. This auxiliary power has half hourly meters installed. The two auxiliary meters have the IDs: R98HAN757 (aka S36A-VFH-TR01) and R98HAN758 (aka S36A-VFH-TR02). 

Gross 3 HH av. peak generation from Unit 5 on separate days = 141.040 MW
At these three HH times, aux load on Unit 5 = 2.597 MW
Net generation from Unit 5 = 138.443 MW
DID-23.Location and Post Code: Esso Petroleum Company,Limited, Oil Refinery at Esso Refinery - Fawley - Southampton - Hampshire - SO45 1TX - United Kingdom

DRX_6G.Description of CMU Components: This CMU component is an open cycle gas turbine unit fuelled by distillate with BMU identifier T_DRAXX-10G under the BSC. The net output of the CMU component will be the metered output for T_DRAXX-10G. This component is a self-supporting unit that does not require station imports to operate. Therefore no auxiliary load is attributed to this component.

This CMU component is an open cycle gas turbine unit fuelled by distillate with BMU identifier T_DRAXX-12G under the BSC. The net output of the CMU component will be the metered output for T_DRAXX-12G. This component is a self-supporting unit that does not require station imports to operate. Therefore no auxiliary load is attributed to this component.

This CMU component is a boiler turbine unit at Drax Power Station with BMU identifier T_DRAXX-6 under the BSC. The metering for this unit is an aggregation of GEN6 and UT6.The net output of the CMU component will be the metered output for T_DRAXX-6 less the auxiliary load. The auxiliary load for Drax Power Station is measured by 2 BMUs: E_MDRX001 and  E_MDRX002. E_MDRX001 is an aggregation of meters S.T.1A: S.T.1B: S.T.2A: S.T.2B. E_MDRX002 is an aggregation of the FGD Transformers shown on the diagram as 3 4 5&6. The auxiliary load will be apportioned equally between the 6 main units at Drax Power Station therefore this component should take 1/6th of this imported power away from it’s gross net generation to give net output.
